The global furfural market is expected to witness significant growth by the year 2030. The market is segmented based on raw materials, applications, and end-use industries. By raw material, the market is categorized into corn cob, rice husk, sugarcane bagasse, and others. The corn cob segment is expected to dominate the market due to its abundant availability and relatively low cost. In terms of applications, the market is segmented into pharmaceuticals, solvents, furfural alcohol, and others. The pharmaceuticals segment is anticipated to showcase substantial growth owing to the increasing demand for furfural in drug formulations. Lastly, based on end-use industries, the market is segmented into the chemical industry, agriculture, pharmaceuticals, and others.

